headline: Why GE Aerospace Stock Topped the Market Today
summary: On news of a new contract with a rock-steady arm of the U.S. government, investors loaded up on storied industrial company GE Aerospace (NYSE: GE) stock during Monday's trading session.  After the market close on Friday, GE Aerospace announced it signed a contract with the U.S. Air Force worth up to $5 billion.  In the press release touting the latest deal for the engine, GE Aerospace didn't hesitate to point out that the F110 has logged over 11 million flight hours in total.
